As a seasoned web developer with more than
12 years of industry experience. I have a strong
enthusiasm for simplifying difficult technical ideas
into concepts that are simply understood.

element.text:
As VP Engineering of Live Nation (Video Network)
I direct the technological vision of my division as we 
expand into wider digital distribution across
all major platforms.

Developed and delivered scalable solutions to clients using 
broad knowledge of front-end and backend technologies.

Streamlined client asset administration by
delivering web interfaces to classify and audit metadata 
for audio assets on YouTube and other platforms

Empowered brands' ability to target consumers attending live
events by leveraging social APIs and machine learning.

Powered social media influencer discovery and partner 
analytics tracking via AWS enabled scraping operations.

Manage lifecycle and development of partner-facing 
financial dashboards

Identify and investigate discrepancies in revenue via 
automated monthly  reporting audit

Manage distribution of client reporting 
and company newsletter

INDMusic was a pioneer in monetizing independent
artists' music on the YouTube platform
As the sole developer, I was key to establishing them
as a player in the YouTube Multichannel Network space.

Design and manage lifecycle accounting system
to parse large reports and allocate client funds
along with ownership splits

Design / Deploy authenticated administrative CMS
and client-facing financial dashboard

Discover 3rd party integrations to enhance our
client offerings and further automate internal 
functions

Accelerated client acquisition by implementing scalable reporting 
infrastructure to parse large csv files into coherent and fully 
transparent client reporting with authenticated dashboard

Custom analytics dashboards were jointly ideated and provided
to record labels for identifying artists with increased engagement
and provided action items for labels to capitalize on recent popularity

Windows Server 2003/2008 administration
and group policy management.

Manage software and hardware upgrades on remote
shipping container vessels

Perform hardware installations and assist
in connections to satellite communications.

Test and orchestrate distribution of regular Windows 
updates via Windows Software Update Service

Introduced scripted automation into the
team workflow. Greatly increasing productivity
with automated software installations and upgrades

Conducted daily stand-up meetings to organize our
pending items. This brought the team together and
positively contributed to morale and team-mindedness

Independently researched / tested and deployed
administrative software after approval. This led
to deployment of software that enabled major savings
by sending alerts of hardware failures on remote vessels

Leveraged APIs of external mail services power front-end tool 
to customize client newsletter and send accounting updates 
and communications

Enrich internal reporting data with 
API-sourced analytics
